Univariate Techniques¶

Mean +/- k * stdev¶

In [11]:
def plot_meanksd(nb_outliers, attributes_names, ks):
    fig = go.Figure()

    outliers_traces = []
    num_steps = len(nb_outliers)

    for i in range(num_steps):
      outliers_traces.append(
          go.Scatter(
            x=ks, y=nb_outliers[i],
            mode='lines',
            name=f'# outliers {attributes_names[i]} based on k')
      )

    fig = go.Figure(data=outliers_traces)

    steps = []
    for i in range(num_steps):
        step = dict(
            method = 'restyle',  
            args = ['visible', [False] * len(fig.data)],
        )

        step['args'][1][i] = True
        
        steps.append(step)

    sliders = [dict(
        steps = steps,
    )]

    fig.update_layout(showlegend=True)
    fig.layout.sliders = sliders
    fig.show()

def plot_outliers(attribute_name, total_non_outliers, total_outliers):
    non_outliers_traces = []
    outliers_traces = []
    num_steps = len(total_non_outliers)

    for i in range(num_steps):
        non_outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_non_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_non_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attribute_name} non outlier',
            marker=dict(color='green')
        ))

        outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attribute_name} outlier',
            marker=dict(color='red')
        ))

    fig = go.Figure(data=non_outliers_traces + outliers_traces)

    steps = []
    for i in range(num_steps):
        step = dict(
            method = 'restyle',  
            args = ['visible', [False] * len(fig.data)],
        )

        step['args'][1][i] = True
        step['args'][1][i + num_steps] = True
        
        steps.append(step)

    sliders = [dict(
        steps = steps,
    )]

    fig.layout.sliders = sliders
    fig.show()

def meanksd(attribute, k):
    attribute = attribute.to_numpy()
    mean = np.mean(attribute)
    stdev = np.std(attribute)

    outlier_left = attribute[attribute < mean - k * stdev]
    outlier_right = attribute[attribute > mean + k * stdev]
    outliers = np.concatenate((outlier_left, outlier_right))

    non_outliers = [x for x in attribute if x not in outliers]

    return non_outliers, outliers, outlier_left.shape[0] + outlier_right.shape[0]

def attributes_meanksd():
    nb_outliers = []
    ks = []
    k_start = 1.5
    n_ks = 10
    k_increment = (2.5 - 1.5) / n_ks

    for k in range(n_ks):
        ks.append(k_start)
        k_start += k_increment

    for i, name in enumerate(data.columns):
        outliers_number = []
        total_non_outliers = []
        total_outliers = []

        for k in ks:
            non_outliers, outliers, outlier_number = meanksd(data[name], k)

            outliers_number.append(outlier_number)
            total_non_outliers.append(non_outliers)
            total_outliers.append(outliers)

        nb_outliers.append(outliers_number)
        plot_outliers(name, total_non_outliers, total_outliers)

    plot_meanksd(nb_outliers, data.columns, ks)

attributes_meanksd()

def plot_iqr(attributes_names, iqrs):
    fig = go.Figure([go.Bar(x=attributes_names, y=iqrs)])
    fig.show()

def plot_outliers(attributes_names, total_non_outliers, total_outliers):
    non_outliers_traces = []
    outliers_traces = []
    num_steps = len(attributes_names)

    for i in range(num_steps):
        non_outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_non_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_non_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attributes_names[i]} non outlier',
            marker=dict(color='green')
        ))

        outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attributes_names[i]} outlier',
            marker=dict(color='red')
        ))

    fig = go.Figure(data=non_outliers_traces + outliers_traces)

    steps = []
    for i in range(num_steps):
        step = dict(
            method = 'restyle',  
            args = ['visible', [False] * len(fig.data)],
        )

        step['args'][1][i] = True
        step['args'][1][i + num_steps] = True
        
        steps.append(step)

    sliders = [dict(
        steps = steps,
    )]

    fig.update_layout(showlegend=True)
    fig.layout.sliders = sliders
    fig.show()

def iqr(attribute):
    Q3, Q1 = np.percentile(attribute, [75 ,25])
    IQR = Q3 - Q1

    lb = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    ub = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    outlier_left = attribute[attribute < lb]
    outlier_right = attribute[attribute > ub]
    outliers = np.concatenate((outlier_left, outlier_right))

    non_outliers = [x for x in attribute if x not in outliers]

    return non_outliers, outliers, outlier_left.shape[0] + outlier_right.shape[0]

def attributes_iqr():
    iqrs = []
    total_non_outliers = []
    total_outliers = []

    for name in data.columns:
        non_outliers, outliers, o_iqr = iqr(data[name])
        
        iqrs.append(o_iqr)
        total_non_outliers.append(non_outliers)
        total_outliers.append(outliers)

    plot_outliers(data.columns, total_non_outliers, total_outliers)
    plot_iqr(data.columns, iqrs)

attributes_iqr()

Ionosphere dataset¶

In [243]:
data = data_ionosphere_X
data_y = data_ionosphere_y

def precision_recall(y_true, y_pred):
    accuracy = float(sum(y_pred == y_true)) / len(y_true)
    truePositive = sum([1 if y_pred[i] == 1 and y_true[i] == 1 else 0 for i in range(len(y_pred))])
    trueNegative = sum([1 if y_pred[i] == 0 and y_true[i] == 0 else 0 for i in range(len(y_pred))])
    falsePositive = sum([1 if y_pred[i] == 1 and y_true[i] == 0 else 0 for i in range(len(y_pred))])
    falseNegative = sum([1 if y_pred[i] == 0 and y_true[i] == 1 else 0 for i in range(len(y_pred))])

    precision = truePositive / (truePositive + falsePositive + 1e-4)
    recall = truePositive / (truePositive + falseNegative + 1e-4)

    return precision, recall

Univariate Techniques¶

Mean +/- k * stdev¶

In [246]:
def plot_meanksd(nb_outliers, attributes_names, ks):
    fig = go.Figure()

    outliers_traces = []
    num_steps = len(nb_outliers)

    for i in range(num_steps):
      outliers_traces.append(
          go.Scatter(
            x=ks, y=nb_outliers[i],
            mode='lines',
            name=f'# outliers {attributes_names[i]} based on k')
      )

    fig = go.Figure(data=outliers_traces)

    steps = []
    for i in range(num_steps):
        step = dict(
            method = 'restyle',  
            args = ['visible', [False] * len(fig.data)],
        )

        step['args'][1][i] = True
        
        steps.append(step)

    sliders = [dict(
        steps = steps,
    )]

    fig.update_layout(showlegend=True)
    fig.layout.sliders = sliders
    fig.show()

def plot_outliers(attribute_name, total_non_outliers, total_outliers, total_labels):
    non_outliers_traces = []
    outliers_traces = []
    num_steps = len(total_non_outliers)

    for i in range(num_steps):
        non_outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_non_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_non_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attribute_name} non outlier',
            marker=dict(color='green')
        ))

        outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attribute_name} outlier',
            marker=dict(color='red')
        ))

    fig = go.Figure(data=non_outliers_traces + outliers_traces)

    steps = []
    for i in range(num_steps):
        precision, recall = precision_recall(data_y, total_labels[i])
        step = dict(
            method = 'update',  
            args=[
                  {"visible": [False] * len(fig.data)},
                  {"title": f"Precision: {precision}, Recall: {recall}"}
            ],
        )

        step['args'][0]["visible"][i] = True
        step['args'][0]["visible"][i + num_steps] = True
        
        steps.append(step)

    sliders = [dict(
        steps = steps,
    )]

    fig.layout.sliders = sliders
    fig.show()

def meanksd(attribute, k):
    attribute = attribute.to_numpy()
    mean = np.mean(attribute)
    stdev = np.std(attribute)

    outlier_left = attribute[attribute < mean - k * stdev]
    outlier_right = attribute[attribute > mean + k * stdev]
    outliers = np.concatenate((outlier_left, outlier_right))

    non_outliers = [x for x in attribute if x not in outliers]
    labels = [1 if x in outliers else 0 for x in attribute]

    return non_outliers, outliers, outlier_left.shape[0] + outlier_right.shape[0], labels

def attributes_meanksd():
    nb_outliers = []
    ks = []
    k_start = 1.5
    n_ks = 10
    k_increment = (2.5 - 1.5) / n_ks

    for k in range(n_ks):
        ks.append(k_start)
        k_start += k_increment

    for i, name in enumerate(data.columns):
        outliers_number = []
        total_non_outliers = []
        total_outliers = []
        total_labels = []

        for k in ks:
            non_outliers, outliers, outlier_number, labels = meanksd(data[name], k)

            outliers_number.append(outlier_number)
            total_non_outliers.append(non_outliers)
            total_outliers.append(outliers)
            total_labels.append(labels)

        nb_outliers.append(outliers_number)
        plot_outliers(name, total_non_outliers, total_outliers, total_labels)

    plot_meanksd(nb_outliers, data.columns, ks)

attributes_meanksd()

def plot_iqr(attributes_names, iqrs):
    fig = go.Figure([go.Bar(x=attributes_names, y=iqrs)])
    fig.show()

def plot_outliers(attributes_names, total_non_outliers, total_outliers, total_labels):
    non_outliers_traces = []
    outliers_traces = []
    num_steps = len(attributes_names)

    for i in range(num_steps):
        non_outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_non_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_non_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attributes_names[i]} non outlier',
            marker=dict(color='green')
        ))

        outliers_traces.append(go.Scatter(
            x=total_outliers[i],
            y=np.zeros(len(total_outliers[i])),
            mode='markers',
            name=f'{attributes_names[i]} outlier',
            marker=dict(color='red')
        ))

    fig = go.Figure(data=non_outliers_traces + outliers_traces)

    steps = []
    for i in range(num_steps):
        precision, recall = precision_recall(data_y, total_labels[i])
        step = dict(
            method = 'update',  
            args=[
                  {"visible": [False] * len(fig.data)},
                  {"title": f"Precision: {precision}, Recall: {recall}"}
            ],
        )

        step['args'][0]["visible"][i] = True
        step['args'][0]["visible"][i + num_steps] = True
        
        steps.append(step)

    sliders = [dict(
        steps = steps,
    )]

    fig.update_layout(showlegend=True)
    fig.layout.sliders = sliders
    fig.show()

def iqr(attribute):
    Q3, Q1 = np.percentile(attribute, [75 ,25])
    IQR = Q3 - Q1

    lb = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    ub = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    outlier_left = attribute[attribute < lb]
    outlier_right = attribute[attribute > ub]
    outliers = np.concatenate((outlier_left, outlier_right))

    non_outliers = [x for x in attribute if x not in outliers]
    labels = [1 if x in outliers else 0 for x in attribute]

    return non_outliers, outliers, outlier_left.shape[0] + outlier_right.shape[0], labels

def attributes_iqr():
    iqrs = []
    total_non_outliers = []
    total_outliers = []
    total_labels = []

    for name in data.columns:
        non_outliers, outliers, o_iqr, labels = iqr(data[name])
        
        iqrs.append(o_iqr)
        total_non_outliers.append(non_outliers)
        total_outliers.append(outliers)
        total_labels.append(labels)

    plot_outliers(data.columns, total_non_outliers, total_outliers, total_labels)
    plot_iqr(data.columns, iqrs)

attributes_iqr()
